01:24.358 --> 01:27.425
Hey, Dave, take a look
at this, would you?

01:27.427 --> 01:30.228
This arrived
at my house last night.

01:30.230 --> 01:32.781
It's a gift
from Harrison Scott.

01:32.783 --> 01:35.600
Your buddy from Vietnam.

01:35.602 --> 01:38.403
"Appreciate everything
you've done for me."

01:38.405 --> 01:41.456
The grips are a replica
of the Vietnam War Memorial.

01:41.458 --> 01:42.624
It's beautiful.

01:42.626 --> 01:43.942
It's expensive.

01:43.944 --> 01:45.794
What's the matter?

01:45.796 --> 01:47.111
A gift like this

01:47.113 --> 01:48.997
would practically drain
all of Harrison's savings.

01:48.999 --> 01:51.416
Now, if you're trying
to get yourself back on your feet,

01:51.418 --> 01:53.051
why would you do something
like that?

01:53.053 --> 01:54.336
You talk to him?

01:54.338 --> 01:55.787
I left 3 messages
where he lives

01:55.789 --> 01:57.288
at New Directions
for Veterans.

01:57.290 --> 01:58.606
He hasn't returned
my calls.

01:58.608 --> 02:00.308
That's only been
since last night.

02:00.310 --> 02:01.626
I phoned his job
this morning.

02:01.628 --> 02:04.929
He hasn't shown up for work
the past two days, either.

02:04.931 --> 02:07.315
I'm worried, Aaron.

02:07.317 --> 02:10.568
Why don't you go out
to Los Angeles and check on him.

02:10.570 --> 02:11.736
What about our caseload?

02:11.738 --> 02:13.638
It'll be fine.
You've got leave coming.

02:13.640 --> 02:15.607
You should go.

02:16.475 --> 02:17.909
Maybe I'll do that.

02:17.911 --> 02:19.110
Thank you.

02:19.112 --> 02:20.829
Sure.

02:32.091 --> 02:34.292
It's staged. They got people
on those programs

02:34.294 --> 02:35.760
they know are gonna fight.

02:35.762 --> 02:37.796
You should've seen
that guy's wife

02:37.798 --> 02:40.331
when he brought his two girlfriends
out on the stage.

02:40.333 --> 02:43.101
Hoo hoo hoo. Punches
flying everywhere.

02:43.103 --> 02:44.886
It's a TV show.

02:44.888 --> 02:46.388
It's fake.

02:46.390 --> 02:49.607
Whoa. Your ass just
got checkmated, homes.

02:49.609 --> 02:51.509
It's checkers, not chess.

02:51.511 --> 02:52.777
King me.

02:52.779 --> 02:55.947
Well, here's the
problem, your majesty.

02:55.949 --> 02:57.816
This right here
where you're playing--

02:57.818 --> 02:58.950
this is our office.

02:58.952 --> 03:01.319
You want to come here,
play a little game,

03:01.321 --> 03:02.654
you gotta pay us rent.

03:02.656 --> 03:03.638
I said king me.

03:03.640 --> 03:05.457
I ain't kidding,
old-timer.

03:05.459 --> 03:07.709
Cough it up, wallet and watch,
both of you.

03:07.711 --> 03:11.663
I faced a lot worse
than you in Korea.

03:11.665 --> 03:13.832
You two-bit punks
don't scare me.

03:13.834 --> 03:16.200
Oh, yeah?

03:17.303 --> 03:19.254
Well, I can get
a whole lot scarier

03:19.256 --> 03:20.338
than this, grandpa.

03:34.236 --> 03:36.053
What's going on?

03:36.055 --> 03:38.055
We've got a possible
spree killer in Cleveland.

03:38.057 --> 03:40.075
Details are sketchy,
but 90 minutes ago

03:40.077 --> 03:42.444
a man shot and killed
two gang members

03:42.446 --> 03:44.395
at a park on the
outskirts of the city.

03:44.397 --> 03:45.149
Why are we thinking spree?

03:45.174 --> 03:47.174
I mean, gang members
shoot each other all the time.

03:47.334 --> 03:48.917
Because a third gang
member fled the scene,

03:48.919 --> 03:51.336
the shooter hunted him
down at a gas station

03:51.338 --> 03:52.720
over a mile away
to finish the job.

03:52.722 --> 03:54.072
Not your typical M.O.
for a gang shooting.

03:54.074 --> 03:55.540
Oh, and there's more.

03:55.542 --> 03:57.074
After the third
gang member was killed,

03:57.076 --> 03:59.544
a fourth person was shot
and killed at a bus stop

03:59.546 --> 04:01.880
less than a half a mile
away from the gas station.

04:01.882 --> 04:02.881
Also gang related?

04:02.883 --> 04:04.015
I don't know.
Details still coming in.

04:04.017 --> 04:06.101
4 homicides, 3 locations,
all within 90 minutes.

04:06.103 --> 04:07.519
We need to hurry.
Wheels up in 15.

04:07.521 --> 04:09.587
I'll let Morgan know.

04:34.947 --> 04:38.282
Can I help you
with something, sir?

04:38.284 --> 04:40.418
How much ammunition
can I buy?

04:40.420 --> 04:42.086
Well, depends
how much you need.

04:45.290 --> 04:47.559
Those.

04:50.146 --> 04:53.064
That's 19.95.

04:53.066 --> 04:55.633
I'm gonna need
a lot more than that.

04:55.635 --> 04:57.101
Ok.

